// –ê–±—Å—Ç—Ä–∞–∫—Ç–Ω–æ–µ —Å–∏–Ω—Ç–∞–∫—Å–∏—á–µ—Å–∫–æ–µ –¥–µ—Ä–µ–≤–æ
typedef enum {
    NODE_INT,
    NODE_FLOAT,
    NODE_STRING,
    NODE_IDENT,
    NODE_BINOP,
    NODE_CALL,
    NODE_FUNC,
    NODE_IF,
    NODE_WHILE
} NodeType;

typedef struct ASTNode {
    NodeType type;
    union {
        int int_val;
        double float_val;
        char* str_val;
        struct {
            struct ASTNode* left;
            struct ASTNode* right;
            int op;  // '+', '-', '*', '/'
        } binop;
        struct {
            char* name;
            struct ASTNode** args;
            int arg_count;
        } call;
    };
} ASTNode;

// –ì–µ–Ω–µ—Ä–∞—Ü–∏—è –∫–æ–¥–∞
void codegen_x64(ASTNode* node, FILE* out) {
    switch (node->type) {
        case NODE_BINOP:
            codegen_x64(node->binop.left, out);
            fprintf(out, "  push rax\n");
            codegen_x64(node->binop.right, out);
            fprintf(out, "  pop rbx\n");
            if (node->binop.op == '+') {
                fprintf(out, "  add rax, rbx\n");
            }
            break;
    }
}

